	<h1 style="text-align:left" id="part1">Text</h1>
	<p>To add text to a document, you must use this code in the .html file:</p>
	<blockquote><span><code class="w3-codespan">&lt;p&gt;</code></span></blockquote>
	<p>Followed by your line of text. Finally close the whole thing off with a:
		<blockquote><span><code class="w3-codespan">&lt;/p&gt;</code></span></blockquote>
		<p>This is the most simple line of code in a website, and this can also be designed to look much better with a little bit of CSS.</p>

		<br><br><br>
		<h1 style="text-align:left">CSS</h1>
		<p>To design your text, you add code in the <code class="w3-codespan">&lt;p&gt;</code> like this:</p>
		<blockquote><span><code class="w3-codespan">&lt;p style="<i>property:value</i>; "&gt;</code></span></blockquote>



